menuconfig L1_MIDDLEWARE_01_MODULE_06_HARDTIMESTAMP_EN
    bool "ENABLE: L1_MIDDLEWARE_01_MODULE_06_HARDTIMESTAMP_EN"
    default n
    help
        Enable hardware timestamp module that provides microsecond-level timestamp functionality.
        When enabled:
        - Automatically initializes hardware SysTick for precise timing
        - Uses SysTick registers (SysTick->VAL, SysTick->LOAD) for microsecond precision
        - Provides systime_now_us() for high-resolution timestamp
        - Supports both STM32 and AT32 MCUs
        
        When disabled:
        - Falls back to rt_tick_get() conversion for basic timing
        - No hardware initialization required

